{"title_page": "Hari Hari Churiyaan", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Hari Hari Churiyaan\n| image                =\n| caption              = \n| genre                = [[Family drama]]<br>[[Romance film|Love Story]]\n| writer               = [[Jahanzeb Qamar]]\n| director             = Syed Atif Hussain\n| starring             = [[Aiman Khan]]<br>Wahaj Ali\n| theme_music_composer = Waqar Ali\n| opentheme            = [[Rahat Fateh Ali Khan]]\n| composer             = \n| country              = [[Pakistan]]\n| language             = [[Urdu]]\n| num_seasons          = \n| num_episodes         = 28\n| producer             = Zeeshan Khan\n| company              = TNI Productions\n| location             = [[Nathia Gali]] ,[[Pakistan]]\n| runtime              = Approx 40 Minutes\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|08|01}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|df=yes|2018|02|07}}\n| network              = [[Geo Entertainment]]\n}}\n'''''Hari Hari Churiyaan''''' is a Pakistani drama serial written by [[Jahanzeb Qamar]] and directed by [[Waada (TV series)|Waada]] fame  director Syed Atif Hussain. It stars [[Aiman Khan]], [[Hassan Ahmed (actor)|Hassan Ahmed]] and Wahaj Ali in lead.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/218270-Drama-Serial-HARI-HARI-CHOORIAN-to-Hit-TV-Screens-Soon|title=Hari Hari Churiyaan to hit screens soon|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en-US}}</ref> The drama was first aired 1 August 2017 on [[Geo Entertainment]], where it aired every Tuesday at 8:00 P.M.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hipinpakistan.com/news/1152608|title=Aiman Khan next is Hari Hari Churiyaan|last=Anas|first=Khan|work=HIP|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==I also don't know\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Aiman Khan]] as Aiman\n*Wahaj Ali as Ali\n*[[Hassan Ahmed (actor)|Hassan Ahmed]] as Waqar\n*[[Sajid Hassan]] as Fasahat\n*[[Mehmood Aslam]] as Shujat (Aiman's father)\n*[[Shagufta Ejaz]] as Surraya (Aiman's mother)\n*Natasha Ali as Zunaira\n*[[Javeria Abbasi]] as Sheeza\n*Hardy Firdousi as Gul Khan\n*Rabia Tabbassum as Bilqees\n*[[Nazli Nasr]] as Saleema\n*Faria Shaikh as Maheen\n*[[Asad Siddiqui]] as Kashan\n*Naushaba Bashir as Najma\n*Fauzia Mushtaq as Shehnaz (Ali's grandmother)\n*Ali Deswali as Faraz\n*Ali Butt as Zai \n*Sharmeen Tayyab as Guddi Baji\n*Maria Khan as Nausheen\n*Khalid Butt as Hashim\n*Sabahat Ali Bukhari as Salma\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2017 establishments in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Pakistani television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Hari Hari Churiyaan\n| image                =\n| caption              = \n| genre                = [[Family drama]]<br>[[Romance film|Love Story]]\n| writer               = [[Jahanzeb Qamar]]\n| director             = Syed Atif Hussain\n| starring             = [[Aiman Khan]]<br>Wahaj Ali\n| theme_music_composer = Waqar Ali\n| opentheme            = [[Rahat Fateh Ali Khan]]\n| composer             = \n| country              = [[Pakistan]]\n| language             = [[Urdu]]\n| num_seasons          = \n| num_episodes         = 28\n| producer             = Zeeshan Khan\n| company              = TNI Productions\n| location             = [[Nathia Gali]] ,[[Pakistan]]\n| runtime              = Approx 40 Minutes\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|08|01}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|df=yes|2018|02|07}}\n| network              = [[Geo Entertainment]]\n}}\n'''''Hari Hari Churiyaan''''' is a Pakistani drama serial written by [[Jahanzeb Qamar]] and directed by [[Waada (TV series)|Waada]] fame  director Syed Atif Hussain. It stars [[Aiman Khan]], [[Hassan Ahmed (actor)|Hassan Ahmed]] and Wahaj Ali in lead.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/218270-Drama-Serial-HARI-HARI-CHOORIAN-to-Hit-TV-Screens-Soon|title=Hari Hari Churiyaan to hit screens soon|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en-US}}</ref> The drama was first aired 1 August 2017 on [[Geo Entertainment]], where it aired every Tuesday at 8:00 P.M.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hipinpakistan.com/news/1152608|title=Aiman Khan next is Hari Hari Churiyaan|last=Anas|first=Khan|work=HIP|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n==Cast==\n*[[Aiman Khan]] as Aiman\n*Wahaj Ali as Ali\n*[[Hassan Ahmed (actor)|Hassan Ahmed]] as Waqar\n*[[Sajid Hassan]] as Fasahat\n*[[Mehmood Aslam]] as Shujat (Aiman's father)\n*[[Shagufta Ejaz]] as Surraya (Aiman's mother)\n*Natasha Ali as Zunaira\n*[[Javeria Abbasi]] as Sheeza\n*Hardy Firdousi as Gul Khan\n*Rabia Tabbassum as Bilqees\n*[[Nazli Nasr]] as Saleema\n*Faria Shaikh as Maheen\n*[[Asad Siddiqui]] as Kashan\n*Naushaba Bashir as Najma\n*Fauzia Mushtaq as Shehnaz (Ali's grandmother)\n*Ali Deswali as Faraz\n*Ali Butt as Zai \n*Sharmeen Tayyab as Guddi Baji\n*Maria Khan as Nausheen\n*Khalid Butt as Hashim\n*Sabahat Ali Bukhari as Salma\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2017 establishments in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Pakistani television series]]\n", "name_user": "2405:204:383:531a:716:ad1f:9401:324e", "label": "vandal", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hari_Hari_Churiyaan"}
{"title_page": "Torneo de Promoci\u00f3n y Reserva", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league\n| logo       =\n| pixels     =\n| country    = {{PER}}\n| founded    =  {{Start date and age|2010}} \n|first       = [[2010 Torneo de Promoci\u00f3n y Reserva|2010]]\n| teams      = 18\n| promotion  =\n| relegation =\n| levels     =\n| domest_cup =\n| confed_cup =\n| champions  = [[Sporting Cristal]]  ([[2019 Torneo de Promoci\u00f3n y Reserva|2019]])\n| season     =\n| current    = [[2020 Torneo de Promoci\u00f3n y Reserva|2020 season]]\n| most successful club = [[Sporting Cristal]] (3 titles)\n| website    = \n| tv         = CMD\n}}\n\nThe '''Torneo de Promoci\u00f3n y Reserva''' is a youth football league in [[Peru]] for the Peruvian football teams in the [[Peruvian Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Liga 1]]. The league made its debut in 2010.\n\nThe league covers has certain rules involving under age players and benefits for the senior teams. Each team must have at least three players that are at the most 19 years old. The rest of the team can be made up of players that are at the most 21 years old; however, each team has the option to have up to three players that are over the age of 21. The winning reserve team awards their senior club 2 points while the runners-up awards its senior team 1 point.\n\n==Teams==\nA total of 20 teams have been confirmed to play in the 2020 Liga 1.\n\n===Stadia and locations===\n\n{{location map+ |Peru |float=right |width=400 |caption=Locations of the 2020 Liga 1 teams |places=\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-9.929464 |long=-76.239714 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Alianza Universidad|Alianza&nbsp;Universidad]]</div>|mark=Arrows 12x12 w.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-5.2 |long=-80.633333 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Atl\u00e9tico Grau|Grau]]</div>|mark=Arrows 12x12 w.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-8.27689 |long=-77.29648 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Deportivo Llacuabamba|Llacuabamba]]</div>|mark=Arrows 12x12 w.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-13.525 |long=-71.972222 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Cienciano]]<br> [[Real Garcilaso]]</div>|mark=Arrows 12x12 w.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-6.762961 |long=-79.836614 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[FC Carlos Stein|Carlos Stein]]</div>|position=left|mark=Arrows 12x12 e.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-7.164444 |long=-78.510556 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Universidad T\u00e9cnica de Cajamarca|UTC]]</div>|position=left|mark=Arrows 12x12 e.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-13.163056 |long=-74.224444 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Ayacucho FC|Ayacucho]]</div>|mark=Arrows 12x12 w.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-16.398822 |long=-71.536883 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[FBC Melgar|Melgar]]</div>|mark=Arrows 12x12 e.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-15.490833 |long=-70.126944 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Escuela Municipal Deportivo Binacional|Binacional]]</div>|mark=Arrows 12x12 e.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-12.066667 |long=-75.216667 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Sport&nbsp;Huancayo]]</div>|mark=Arrows 12x12 w.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-8.112 |long=-79.0288 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">{{nowrap|[[Carlos A. Mannucci]]}}<br>[[Club Deportivo Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo|U.&nbsp;C\u00e9sar&nbsp;Vallejo]]</div>|position=left|mark=Arrows 12x12 w.svg}}\n{{location map~ |Peru |lat=-12.043333 |long=-77.028333 |label= <div style=\"font-size:80%;\">[[Alianza Lima]]<br />[[Academia Cantolao|Cantolao]]<br />[[Deportivo Municipal|Dep. Municipal]]<br />[[Sport Boys]]<br />[[Sporting Cristal]]<br />[[Universidad San Mart\u00edn de Porres|U. San Mart\u00edn]]<br />[[Club Universitario de Deportes|Universitario]]</div>|position=left|mark=Arrows 12x12 ne.svg}}\n}}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Team\n! City\n! Stadium\n! Capacity<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fussballtempel.net/conmebol/PER.html |first=Gunther |last=Lades |title=Peru |work=web